· Group sparsity loss: It is inspired by spectral clustering where block diagonal similarity matrix is exploited for representation learning (Ng et al., 2002). Group sparsity is itself an effective feature selection method. In Huang et al. (2014), the hidden units were divided into G groups, where G is the assumed number of clusters. When given a data point xi the obtained representation has the form {g(xi)}gG=1. Thus the loss can be defined as follows:

