of many of these methods. Using this taxonomy and the summary of previous methods, generating new methods is clearer and easier and can be done by creating new combinations of the taxonomy's building blocks. Moreover, we present a new method to the field, which is based on such a new combination. Our method overcomes the limitations of several previous ones, approaches state-ofthe-art performance and performs better in some cases.
